Author: fatpigeon_
Text: Big mood, it’s harder and more frustrating the less you have to lose, Having the scale go up 2lbs because of bloating is much more devastating when you have 5lbs to lose vs. 10, 20, etc.

Author: whitecabinets
Text: Wow are you me? I started seriously restricting this week, and I’m on my pseudo IUD period but weigh two more pounds despite being at like 600-900 calories a day. Like I don’t expect to lose 5 a week or anything but Jesus Christ I’ve been within the same 3 pounds for over a year. HW and LW. It’s ridiculous. I just want to lose and keep it off.
